This project has a graphify knowledge graph at `graphify-out/`.

**Before any codebase exploration** (architecture questions, file lookup, understanding system relationships):
1. Read `graphify-out/GRAPH_REPORT.md` — god nodes and community structure tell you where things live
2. If `graphify-out/wiki/index.md` exists, navigate it instead of reading raw files
3. Only fall back to glob/grep/read if the graph is missing or doesn't answer the question

**Before ending any session** in which you modified code files:
- Run `graphify update .` to keep the graph current (AST-only, no API cost)
